      "devata": "Bhagavan Shambhu",
      "sanskrit": "",
      "english": "'Srotasyah'—residing in the current (srotas/flow). 'Dvipyah'—residing on an island (dvipa) in the middle of water. Here, in one single Yajus, two 'cha' particles are recited for the sake of conjunction, to connect the word 'Namah' (salutation) separately to the two words ending in the fourth case. (15)\n\n|| Thus in the Vedartha-prakasha, the commentary on the Yajur-samhita composed by Sayanacharya-Madhava, in the fourth Kanda, fifth Prapathaka, the commentary on the Sri Rudram, ends the Fifth Anuvaka. ||\n..."
    },
    "bhatta_bhaskara": {
      "rishi": "Bhagavan Shambhu",
      "chandas": "Mahavirat",
      "devata": "Bhagavan Shambhu",
      "dhyana": {
        "sanskrit": "भस्मोद्धासितसर्वाङ्गजटामण्डलमण्डितम् । ध्यायेत्रयक्षं वृषारूढं गणेश्वरयुतं हरम् ॥",
        "english": "May one meditate on Hara, who has three eyes, is seated on a bull, accompanied by the lord of hosts (Ganesha), and whose entire body is smeared with ashes and adorned with a crown of matted hair."
      },
